### RxDB: Define and Add a 'todos' Collection Schema

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/articles/local-first-future.md

Adds a 'todos' collection to the RxDB database with a defined JSON schema. The schema specifies fields like `id`, `title`, `done`, and `timestamp`, with `id` as the primary key. This setup is for a simple to-do list application.

```typescript
await db.addCollections({
  todos: {
    schema: {
      version: 0,
      primaryKey: 'id',
      type: 'object',
      properties: {
        id:        { type: 'string', maxLength: 100 },
        title:     { type: 'string' },
        done:      { type: 'boolean' },
        timestamp: { type: 'string' }
      },
      required: ['id', 'title', 'done', 'timestamp']
    }
  }
});
```

