### Define RxDB Schema with Required Primary Key

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs/releases/10.0.0.html

Illustrates how to define a RxDB schema, enforcing the requirement of a primary key. The `primaryKey` property must be set at the top level of the schema. This change improves type safety and clarity when using RxDB with TypeScript.

```typescript
const mySchema: RxJsonSchema<MyDocumentData> = {
    version: 0,
    primaryKey: 'passportId',
    type: 'object',
    properties: {
        passportId: {
            type: 'string'
        }
    },
    // primaryKey is always required
    required: ['passportId']
}
```

