### Configure Server-Only Fields for Replication Endpoint (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/rx-server.md

This TypeScript example demonstrates how to configure `serverOnlyFields` for an RxDB replication endpoint. The field `my-secrets` is designated as server-only, meaning clients cannot see or modify it. This requires that the server schema might differ from the client schema.

```typescript
const endpoint = await server.addReplicationEndpoint({
    name: 'my-endpoint',
    collection: col,
    // here the field 'my-secretss' is defined to be server-only
    serverOnlyFields: ['my-secrets']
});
```

